docs.abstract: Investors are fleeing emerging markets over fears of Chinese currency turbulence and global slowdown, shaking big asset management companies that emphasized third world investments for their higher returns; record $105 billion was withdrawn from global mutual funds in 2015, with United States-based asset managers accounting for 26 percent.
